The paper deals with the problem of throughput allocation in IEEE 802.11 Wireless LANs, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also presents simulation results, which involve multimedia traffic, suggesting cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible sub-category. The proposed algorithm aims to ensure fairness among the stations, which is a characteristic of control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper deals with proportional fairness, which is a concept related to optimization and algorithms, making cs.PF (Performance) a possible sub-category.
